The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Manik Goswami, elder brother of Chuni, passed away on Thursday morning at a city nursing home. Goswami, 75, who was suffering from a cardiac-related problem was the president of the Bengal Tennis Association (BTA). He was also the life vice-president of the AITA.       
	The veteran, who served Mohun Bagan both as a footballer and cricketer, also won the national veterans champion in tennis, twice partnering Akhtar Ali and Hiralal Das.                       
